    {
      "kind": "parameters",
      "parameters": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The active scope of the search field.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "scope"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The activation style of the search fieldâ€™s scopes.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "activation"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "A view builder that represents the scoping options",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "SwiftUI uses to populate a ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "Picker",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": ".",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "scopes"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To enable people to narrow the scope of their searches, you can",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "create a type that represents the possible scopes, and then create a",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "state variable to hold the current selection. For example, you can",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "scope the product search to just fruits or just vegetables:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "enum ProductScope {",
            "    case fruit",
            "    case vegetable",
            "}",
            "",
            "@State private var scope: ProductScope = .fruit"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Provide a binding to the scope, as well as a view that represents each",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "scope:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "ProductList()",
            "    .searchable(text: $text, tokens: $tokens) { token in",
            "        switch token {",
            "        case .apple: Text(\"Apple\")",
            "        case .pear: Text(\"Pear\")",
            "        case .banana: Text(\"Banana\")",
            "        }",
            "    }",
            "    .searchScopes($scope) {",
            "        Text(\"Fruit\").tag(ProductScope.fruit)",
            "        Text(\"Vegetable\").tag(ProductScope.vegetable)",
            "    }"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "SwiftUI uses this binding and view to add a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "Picker",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " below the search",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "field. In iOS, macOS, and tvOS, the picker appears below the search",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "field when search is active. To ensure that the picker operates",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "correctly, match the type of the scope binding with the type of each",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "viewâ€™s tag. Then condition your search on the current value of the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "scope",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " state property.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "By default, the appearance of scopes varies by platform:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "In iOS and iPadOS, search scopes appear when someone enters text",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "into the search field and disappear when someone cancels the search.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "In macOS, search scopes appear when SwiftUI presents search and",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "disappear when someone cancels the search.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "However, you can use the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "activation",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " parameter with a value of",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "SearchScopeActivation/onTextEntry",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " or",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "SearchScopeActivation/onSearchPresentation",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " to configure this",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "behavior:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            ".searchScopes($scope, activation: .onSearchPresentation) {",
            "    Text(\"Fruit\").tag(ProductScope.fruit)",
            "    Text(\"Vegetable\").tag(ProductScope.vegetable)",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For more information about using searchable modifiers, see",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "doc:Adding-a-search-interface-to-your-app",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
